26/10/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian Orthodox Church Patriarch Pavle has asked to resign from his post, citing poor health, the Holy Synod of the church announced on Friday (October 24th). 
Pavle, 94, plans to be admitted to the Military Medical Academy in Belgrade for hospital treatment on November 13th. 
He has been fighting heart and lung problems for months. 
The Synod plans to meet on November 11th to discuss a possible successor. 
(Reuters, Blic, RTS, B92, AP - 24/10/08)
